snippet.textDisplay:
Favourite moments:

00:19 That rubab coming in
00:35 That Action of applying "Pakkay sur"  
00:58 Nirmal entering the song with her melodious voice.. 
1:15 Is that poison of love really taking her life? Because that face... with her phenomenal delivery of this line..
1:24-1:30 Everything is perfect here. The voice, the arrangement, the lyrics, the meanings of those lyrics, Rubab, drums.. expressions.. EVERYTHING. 
1:49 Rubab is already adding so much to the song. And then there is natasha khan with her magical smile, enjoying whatever she has to add to this song.
2:15 That delivery of "Hayaati" came off as a magical word here.
2:29-2:56 Lyrics are so good for an original song. 
دل نوں سمجھاواں، بہلاواں...(کمال)
And then his facial expressions say "You people have no idea what's about to come yet."
2:56 And then flute is introduced shortly after his lines as a testification. Flute has already indicated that magic is about to happen.
3:30 That immense pleasure... as Ali is leaving for a while..Aahad is so happy with what Nirmal is going to spread out there in the studio.
3:32 Nirmal enters with her beautiful, beautiful lines. Those little hand gestures... That "Phabdi"...Her cute little face.. flute is enhancing the magic that is going on there in the studio..
3:45 That drum arrangement is such beauty, can't be described in words. That little step that Ali does on the beat of drums...👌👌👌 (Always fills me with joy).
3:52 کمال.
 Lyrics are sung so well with the arrangement

چپ کر جا نہ کر شور..
نئیں چلنا تیرا زور..
وس دیاں... وس پیندیاں..ہو دل اجڑے تے مڑ نئیں او وسدا..

That little flavour of begging..that pleading. With such sweetness in her voice is what makes this song so special.
3:52 What Ali is doing shows how well he wants this song to be executed. That courage. Again at 4:02 He is really feeling the song.
4:14-4:24 Those riffs and emphasis on "Na-aa-aa..." ❤. At 4:24 how she slows down lets us know another magic is there to have us mesmerised. 
4:25-Onwards Ali's vocals are tellingly filled with so much joy... and that lays the foundation of that magic.
This part is so well executed. It makes you sway, dance and move along with the rhythm.
4:36 Music suddenly stops. She sings... "او ججانجھر پھبدی نا" رونگٹے کھڑے ہوگئے
(Lil goosebumps moments)
And then one line by him and one by her... goosebumps everywhere. Though i wish this should've gone a little bit longer.
5:11 Him coming back to the mic as she slowly ends her line..👌
5:12 Jindjaani way sohniye... dil tere aasray Chalay.... Beautifully sung.

This song gradually grows on you and once it does, it's hard to not listen to it.❤
